        • [ - ] Queen1 - member since 29-Aug-14

          This game was against my own prediction (1-3). Ajax showed courage and played above their doings, while PSG were underperforming. Despite the fact that PSG had more chances, the real pressure came from Ajax. If Ajax could pull the trigger more often (lets say by a striker like Ibra), they would've won the game. Nonetheless, a 1-1 is an excellent result for Ajax, who are hoping to go through to the knock-out stages this year. Its going to be tough for them, but if they keep this spirit, they might have a chance. As Ajax fan i really hope they do make it ;). Blanc has to scratch behind his ears, because he did'nt anticipate well enough on the encounter. De Boer said he is pleased by the draw, but knowing de Boer, he will tell his players to do better next time, because they had the game, especially in the second half of the match.

          In a neutral point of view, I find this game to be a quality youngsters team vs millionaire established team. PSG are easily favorites but an Ajax win wouldn't be much of a shock since they're not an underdog team, they have promissing quality players (they have a prestigious school after all). However, PSG has invested too much money to let themselves be surprised.

        • [ - ] Queen1 - member since 29-Aug-14

          Since the 10/11 season in CL football, Ajax did never win their first game. Two times they drawed, two times they lost. And they lost their two games against Dortmund (12/13) and Barca (13/14), which are big teams (other two were Lyon and PAOK). Ajax always has problems at the start of the season and especially in European football. They lost key men the last few years (Eriksen, Vertonghen and this season they lost De Jong (c) and Blind) who were all leading in the team. Now they have to build up again with this team and that takes time, which is not given. PSG on the other hand won both their first games (12/13 and 13/14) with confidence (both times 4-1). And they are really stirred up for European prizes. They didn't lose quality, but gain quality every year, with Zlatan as keyman. On the field, Ajax prefers dominant play, while tries the same. I believe PSG will win because of individual skills: 1-3. As Ajax-fan i prefer a win. Hopefully de Boer gives the guys confidence to win ;).
